  <info>
    <title>Managing network using &cockpit;</title>
    <meta name="maintainer" content="shalaka.harne@suse.com" its:translate="no"/>
    <abstract>
      <para>&cockpit; enables you create virtual networks and manage them.</para>
    </abstract>
  </info>
  <section><title>Creating a network</title>
  <procedure><step><para>Navigate to the <guimenu>Virtual machines</guimenu> page and click <guimenu>Networks</guimenu> link.</para></step>
  <step><para>Click <guimenu>Create virtual network</guimenu>.</para>
  <para>In the <guilabel>Create virtual network</guilabel> page, enter the following details:</para>

<itemizedlist><listitem><para>Enter a network name.</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Select the <guimenu>Forward mode</guimenu> and the <guimenu>Device</guimenu> from the drop-down lists.</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Select the <guimenu>IP configuration</guimenu>, then provide the IPv4 and/or IPv6 address and prefix length.</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>To configure a DHCP range, select Set DHCP range and enter the start and end values.</para></listitem>
</itemizedlist></step>
<step><para>Click <guimenu>Create</guimenu>.</para></step>
</procedure></section>

<section><title>Managing network</title>
  <para>To perform any administration task on an existing network, perform the following steps:</para>
<procedure>
<step><para>Navigate to the <guimenu>Virtual machines</guimenu> page and select the <guimenu>Networks</guimenu> link.</para></step>
<step><para>Here you can perform the following actions with existing storage pools:</para>
<variablelist>
  <varlistentry>
          <term>Activate</term>
          <listitem>
            <para>
              Click the <guimenu>Activate</guimenu> button next to the required network.
            </para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>      
  <varlistentry>
          <term>Deactivate</term>
          <listitem>
            <para>
              Click <guimenu>Deactivate</guimenu> next to the network name.
            </para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
        <varlistentry>
          <term>Delete</term>
          <listitem>
            <para>
              In the three-dot menu, select <guimenu>Delete</guimenu>.
            </para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
      </variablelist>
</step>
</procedure></section>
</topic>
